title: Volleyball Roundup: Buckeye Central wins
text:
Volleyball Roundup: Buckeye Central wins Staff report 10:48 p.m. EDT October 22, 2015 STK Stock 
Division I Sectional 
Oregon Clay 3, Madison 0 
The Rams (5-17) were defeated in three sets (15-25, 9-25, 16-25) on Thursday. Kamilla Brown had 11 digs and eight kills, Nikki Harris had nine digs, Taylor Rose had four kills, Kinsey Kriner had 11 assists and Magey Shambre had seven assists 
Division II Sectional 
Upper Sandusky 3, Clear Fork 0 
Clear Fork lost in three sets (11-25, 14-25, 12-25) to Upper Sandusky on Thursday. 
Division III Sectional 
Marion Pleasant 3, Fredericktown 0 
Pleasant defeats Fredericktown in three sets (25-13, 25-23, 25-21) on Thursday during Sectional final tournament action. Pleasant advances to the District Semi-Final at Marion Harding on Tuesday. 
Highland 3, Liberty Union 0 
Highland swept Liberty Union in three sets (25-16, 25-15, 25-20) on Thursday to advance to the Districts. Bailey Santo had six kills and Bridget Oder had 19 digs. 
Division IV Sectional 
Buckeye Central 3, South Central 0 
Buckeye Central defeated South Central in three sets (25-14, 25-12, 25-23) in the Sectional Final on Thursday. 
Sarah Oney led South Central with nine kills and 11 digs, Olivia Keysor had four kills, Maddie Albert had 18 assists and two aces, Hannah Vogel had 14 digs and one ace and Lexi Adams had 10 digs and two blocks. 
Monroeville 3, Crestline 0 
Crestline lost to Monroeville in three sets (8-25, 5-25, 5-25) in the Sectional Final on Thursday. 
Sandusky St. Mary Central Catholic 3, Mansfield Christian 0 
Mansfield Christian lost in three sets (12-25, 19-25, 23-25) in the Sectional Final on Thursday. Read or Share this story: http://ohne.ws/1LQqAVg MORE STORIES
